{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "/second-brain-wiki Add this to my wiki:\n\n# Vector Databases\n\nSpecialized databases that store and query high-dimensional vector embeddings.\nUsed heavily in RAG pipelines and similarity search applications.\n\nKey concepts:\n- Embeddings: dense numerical representations of text/images\n- Cosine similarity: primary distance metric for semantic search\n- HNSW: approximate nearest neighbor algorithm used by most vector DBs\n- Popular options: Pinecone, Weaviate, Qdrant, pgvector\n- Trade-off: speed vs recall (exact search is slow, approximate is fast)"}, "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:40:17.541Z"}
