{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01FZk8dCSFX7w1Z3mvut7YA2", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_015eLFvo65z4ab6dn4qq2VqS", "name": "Edit", "input": {"replace_all": false, "file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-databases.md", "old_string": "## Popular Options\n\n- **ChromaDB** \u2014 open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n- **Pinecone** \u2014 managed service, scales automatically\n- **Weaviate** \u2014 open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n- **Qdrant** \u2014 open-source, Rust-based, high performance", "new_string": "## Popular Options\n\n- **ChromaDB** \u2014 open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n- **Pinecone** \u2014 managed service, scales automatically\n- **Weaviate** \u2014 open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n- **Qdrant** \u2014 open-source, Rust-based, high performance\n- **pgvector** \u2014 PostgreSQL extension; adds vector storage and ANN search to an existing Postgres DB"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 5031, "cache_read_input_tokens": 38090, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 5031, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 8}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "b9ea5e4c-43e6-4437-bf16-7ac47bc8667e", "uuid": "9f4a65b8-6863-41fd-b24e-c1260fbe4445", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrjgH6kCR9iBYPgDpdaN", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:41:00.669Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_015eLFvo65z4ab6dn4qq2VqS","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-databases.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9ea5e4c-43e6-4437-bf16-7ac47bc8667e","uuid":"46d1c30e-96a9-4060-853a-c88a92e8a738","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:41:00.678Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-databases.md","oldString":"## Popular Options\n\n- **ChromaDB** — open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n- **Pinecone** — managed service, scales automatically\n- **Weaviate** — open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n- **Qdrant** — open-source, Rust-based, high performance","newString":"## Popular Options\n\n- **ChromaDB** — open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n- **Pinecone** — managed service, scales automatically\n- **Weaviate** — open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n- **Qdrant** — open-source, Rust-based, high performance\n- **pgvector** — PostgreSQL extension; adds vector storage and ANN search to an existing Postgres DB","originalFile":"# Vector Databases\n\nA vector database stores data as high-dimensional vectors (embeddings) and enables fast similarity search. They are a key component in [RAG](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) pipelines, recommendation systems, and semantic search.\n\n## Popular Options\n\n- **ChromaDB** — open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n- **Pinecone** — managed service, scales automatically\n- **Weaviate** — open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n- **Qdrant** — open-source, Rust-based, high performance\n\n## How They Work\n\n1. Documents are converted to embeddings using a model\n2. Embeddings are indexed for fast nearest-neighbor search\n3. At query time, the query is embedded and compared to stored vectors\n4. The most similar vectors (and their associated documents) are returned\n\n## Use Cases\n\n- [RAG systems](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) for grounding LLM responses\n- Semantic search across large document collections\n- Recommendation engines\n- Image and audio similarity search\n\n## Related\n\n- [Vector Similarity Search](vector-similarity-search.md) — the algorithms (HNSW, IVF) that power the nearest-neighbor queries vector DBs run\n- [Retrieval-Augmented Generation](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) — primary consumer of vector DB retrieval\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/vector-databases.md\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":8,"oldLines":6,"newStart":8,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - **Pinecone** — managed service, scales automatically"," - **Weaviate** — open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)"," - **Qdrant** — open-source, Rust-based, high performance","+- **pgvector** — PostgreSQL extension; adds vector storage and ANN search to an existing Postgres DB"," "," ## How They Work"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
